CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 21, 1946, pg. 13, reads: "COLLEGE SHOWER - It wasn't Christmas last Thursday but students going away to college received many useful gifts at the 'Go - To - College Party' sponsored by the Young People's Department of the Woman's Missionary Society at Bethel AME Parish House. Left to right: Doris Perkins is shown selecting her gift.  Anna Mosby shares the fun with Louise Baker as she 'peaks' into a bag of surprises, and Thelma Denson unties a package she hopes contains nylon stockings.  The fun was in charge of Mary Robinson.  Miss Laura Bell Harris and Mrs. Elsie Meeks were chairmen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Doris Perkins, Anna Mosby, Louise Baker, and Thelma Denson gathered behind wooden table with wrapped gifts, for "Go To College Party" sponsored by Young People's Department of the Woman's Missionary Society at Bethel AME Church
